Considering the nature of standards and attending the industry needs, implementation-orientated active learning methods, such as Project-Based Learning (PBL, http://www.bie.org), provide a student-centered learning environment that is appropriate for the purpose.

SDR development and implementation frameworks, such as the software communications architecture (SCA)—primarily used in military radios [13]—, GNU Radio—primarily used in research and education (http://gnuradio.org)—, and the application layer and operating environment (ALOE)—also used in research and education (http://flexnets.upc.edu)—, have certain features in common with the specifications of wireless

The ALOE tutorial describes the ALOE architecture, tools and services and makes reference to the ALOE Web Site (http://flexnets.upc.edu), where the entire ALOE code base resides and can be downloaded, installed and modified for free.
